'''''Inside HBOâ&euro;&trade;s Game of Thrones: Seasons 3 &amp; 4''''' is a companion book about the ''[[Game of Thrones (TV series)|Game of Thrones]]'' TV series adaptation produced by HBO. It is a sequel to ''[[Inside HBO's Game of Thrones]]'', which provided behind-the-scenes interviews and information about the production of [[Season 1]] and [[Season 2]] of the TV series, and was written by scriptwriter and loremaster [[Bryan Cogman]].

The sequel contains new behind-the-scenes interviews and information from the production of [[Season 3]] and [[Season 4]], and was written by Cat Taylor, the former personal assistant to showrunners [[David Benioff]]Â and [[D.B. Weiss]]. She is best known to fans as the original writer of the &quot;Making Game of Thrones&quot; official HBO production blog (which she stopped writing for by the end of Season 4). The book includes a preface by Benioff and Weiss. It will go on sale in Fall 2014.&lt;ref&gt;[http://watchersonthewall.com/exclusive-preview-inside-hbos-game-thrones-seasons-3-4/ Exclusive preview of Inside HBOâ&euro;&trade;s Game of Thrones: Seasons 3 &amp; 4!]&lt;/ref&gt;
